  "texts": [
    "While binary classification (e.g., \"Is this hateful?",
    "Yes/No\") offers clarity and ease of comparison, it can mask uncertainty and force artificial dichotomies onto nuanced content.",
    "In contrast, probability-based formats or ordinal scales allow for gradation and express uncertainty, which may be more faithful to the complexities of language and social meaning.",
    "However, these richer formats also introduce analytic challenges-such as increased variability across runs or difficulties in benchmarking against human coders.",
    "This tradeoff highlights a central tension in LLM-assisted content analysis: greater flexibility comes at the cost of reduced standardization."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}